Quote: THE PLUNKET SHIELD. At a meeting of the New Zealand Cricket Council the conditions for the Plunket Challenge Shield were adopted, subject to the approval of His Excellency. The shield is to be open for competition amongst all Associations affiliated to the New Zealand Cricket Council, who would allot the shield to the Association whose rep-team is considered to have the best record for the season 1906-07 ...
